## Arman Decisions (context for reviewers)

**Decision A-3 (Fix2): How to detect "table not closed" after all orders are served?**
Chosen: **Modify `closeSession()` in `components/sessionHelpers.js`** to bulk-update all orders of the session to `status: 'closed'`. SOM then filters by `o.status !== 'closed'`. Verified: `closeSession` is used ONLY in SOM (grep confirmed, no usage in PublicMenu/CartView/OrdersList/ClientHome). Rejected: (1) loading TableSessions in SOM — extra query, complexity; (3) local useState flag — not persistent across refresh.

**Decision B-3 (Fix4): Fix all 4 active render branches, legacy branch (line 2346) out of scope.**
Chosen: Fix B1 (677-703), B2 (761-769), B3 (1288-1314), B4 (1374-1398). Legacy fallback on line 2346 stays as-is (rarely used, old code path). Line 2333 (B5) already uses the correct pattern — reviewers should use it as **reference model**.

